HEADWORD: Shebeen
<hw>She*been"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Of Irish origin;
cf. Ir. <ets>seapa</ets> a shop.]</ety> <def>A low public house;
especially, a place where spirits and other excisable liquors are
illegally and privately sold.</def> <mark>[Ireland]</mark><-- similar to
a speakeasy? -->⟦br⟧
